full_summary:
**Government Tender Announcement**
==========================

**Survey Design for Non-Market Valuation Study**
--------------------------------------------

### Tender Details

* **Reference Number**: cb-209-22925425
* **Solicitation Number**: 30004537
* **Publication Date**: Thursday, November 16, 2023
* **Tender Closing Date**: Tuesday, December 19, 2023, 2:00 PM EST
* **Expected Contract Start Date**: Wednesday, December 18, 2024
* **Expected Contract End Date**: Monday, September 30, 2024

### Opportunities

This procurement opportunity is for a Request for Proposal (RFP) under the Invitation Open to All Interested Suppliers (Competitive Shopping Procedure). The contract is for a period of 9 months and is expected to be worth CAD \[see tender documents for estimated cost\].

### Objectives

The successful bidder will develop a statistically valid survey instrument to estimate the non-market economic value of the protection and recovery of several aquatic species at risk. The results of the survey will be used to provide values to support economic analysis for the protection and recovery of endangered and threatened aquatic species.

### Evaluation Criteria

The tender evaluation will be based on a combined rating of technical merit and price.

### Trade Agreements

The proposed contract is open to suppliers who are entitled to participate in the supply of goods or services in Canada under the North American Free Trade Agreement (NAFTA) and the Canada- Korea Free Trade Agreement (CKFTA).

### Notice

Please note that this tender announcement is now expired.

### Additional Resources

You can find the entire tender notice in the attachment link below:
https://canadabuys.canada.ca/sites/default/files/webform/tender_notice/24938/rfp-30004537-survey-design-for-non-market-valuation-study-of-protection-and-recovery-of-aquatic-species-at-risk_0.pdf
